premise_source_doc_sentence: The Spider-Man film series is a superhero film series consisting of Spider-Man  (  2002  )  , Spider-Man 2  (  2004  )  and Spider-Man 3  (  2007  )  .
Spider-Man 3 is a 2007 American superhero film produced by Marvel Studios , and distributed by Columbia Pictures based on the fictional Marvel Comics character Spider-Man .
With a box office total of nearly $ 900 million , Spider-Man 3 stands as the highest-earning in the series and is the 31st highest-grossing film worldwide .

The rights to further films featuring the character were purchased in 1985 , and moved through various production companies and studios before being secured by Sony Pictures Entertainment  (  Columbia Pictures  )  , who hired Sam Raimi to direct Spider-Man  (  2002  )  , Spider-Man 2  (  2004  )  , and Spider-Man 3  (  2007  )  starring Tobey Maguire .
Inspired by the movies Spider-Man , Spider-Man 2 , and Spider-Man 3 , this action/adventure beat 'em up game reinterprets big-screen moments and battles with a humorous twist .
